{% extends "include/base.html.twig" %}

{% block content %}

  <table width='750px' border='0'>
    <tr>
      <td valign='top'>
        <h3 style="color:#CC0000; font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
          {{ 'Bulk Recognition'| trans }}
        </h3>
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
          <p>
          {{ 'Going through an upload on a file by file basis can turn into an almost endless
            task when considering larger packages, such as the Linux kernel, the open
            office source code or the boost library.'| trans }}
          <p>
          {{ 'However, in many projects, the license information will stay the
          same across many files. Then, the idea of bulk-wise processing files is
          obvious considering a high number of files with exactly same license texts.'| trans }}
          <p>
          {{ 'With bulk recognition, the user defines a text phrase and associates a
          license entry or removal in the table of associated licenses for this file. 
          Then, at every file, where the given text is
          found, the application either adds or removes a license entry from the
          license table.'| trans }}
          <p>
          {{ 'The case of removal allows for the correction of scanner findings that are
          found among a number of files. The addition of a license entry will add license
          entry if this license has not been identified by scanner before. '| trans }}
          <p>
          {{ 'Internally, the application will do three things on the files in the scope
          (either entire upload or current folder):'| trans }}
		  <ul>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Match the given text in the files using the Monk text similarity agent.
			Matching requires 100% similarity.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Add a license entry “bulk finding” in the list of licenses associated
			for this file.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Run a decider agent that creates clearing decision if all license entries
			for a file form pairs of scan result and bulk findings.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   </ul>
          <p>
          {{ 'Bulk recognition allows for batch processing all files in the upload at once
          when the licensing text stays the same.'| trans }}
        <h4 style="color:#CC0000; font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
          {{ 'Single License Bulk Recognition'| trans }}
        </h4>
        <p>
        {{ 'The single file bulk recognition is obvious. Imagine the following example
        from zlib (<code>contrib/ dotzlib/ DotZLib/ ChecksumImpl.cs</code>):'| trans }}
        <p>
        <pre>
// © Copyright Henrik Ravn 2004
//
// Use, modification and distribution are subject to the Boost Software License, Version 1.0.
// (See accompanying file LICENSE_1_0.txt or copy at http://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt)
//
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;
using System.Text;

namespace DotZLib ...
        </pre>
        <p>
        {{ 'There are 9 files in zlib with the same header information about licensing.
        The Nomos scanner identifies every occurrence of this header as a BSL-1.0
        licensing. The goal is now to confirm this finding. The bulk scan be used in the
        following way by clicking the button "Bulk Recognition...":'| trans }}
        <ol>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Copy the text phrase <code>Use, modification and distribution are
			subject to the Boost Software License, Version 1.0.</code> from the source
			file display on the right.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Paste the test into the reference text field.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Make sure that the BSL-1.0 (Boost Software License) is selected.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Select “Add License” (plus sign).'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Run bulk scan on the entire upload.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		</ol>
		<p>
        {{ 'As a result, the bulk scan will create a license entry for the files, where
        the text phrase is matching. Then, the decider will see that a (Nomos) scanner
        finding is confirmed by the bulk scan and creates a clearing decision for all
        matching files. '| trans }}
        <h4 style="color:#CC0000; font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
          {{ 'Multi License Bulk Recognition'| trans }}
        </h4>
        <p>
        {{ 'Imagine the following case form zlib ( <code>adler32.c</code> ):'| trans }}
        <p>
        <pre>
/* adler32.c -- compute the Adler-32 checksum of a data stream
 * Copyright (C) 1995-2011 Mark Adler
 * For conditions of distribution and use, see copyright notice in zlib.h
 */

/* @(#) $Id$ */

#include "zutil.h"
        </pre>
        <p>
        {{ 'The Nomos scanner will result in a “zlib possibility” finding, meaning that
        the Nomos does not exectyl now, if the zlib license is actually relevant here. 
        In this case, the user wishes to do:'| trans }}
        <ol>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Remove the zlib-possibility finding.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Add the zlib license as license entry.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		</ol>
		<p>
        {{ 'The way to perform that is the following:'| trans }}
        <ol>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Copy the text phrase from the source file display on the right.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Paste the into the reference text.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Select “Add License” (plus sign).'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Make sure that the zlib license is selected.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Select “Remove License” (minus sign).'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Make sure that the zlib-possibilty is selected.'| trans }}
		   </li>
		   <li>
			{{ 'Run bulk scan on the entire upload.'| trans }}
		   </li>		   
		</ol>
		<p>
        {{ 'The result is a clearing decision set for all files with this statement
        is set automatically.'| trans }}
        </font>
        </td>
      <td><img src="{{ SiteURI }}images/white.png"></td>
    </tr>
  </table>

{% endblock %}